<blockquote>
<p>Isn't that important information?</p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">If you just want to learn about what these things do or how they do it, not really. It might be useful if you were trying to find these in the wild or track their origin, but considering this report has an experiment log that goes pretty far in-depth in regards to what these things do, I doubt that this was written for the people who are assigned to the &quot;secure&quot; part of SCP. In their version, it probably has the containment procedures and description, but the experiment log is redacted or not mentioned at all.</span></p>
<blockquote>
<p>why would subject 0's name or the epicenter of where they were discovered be redacted?</p>
</blockquote>
<p><span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Also, if the name and place are redacted, subject 0 becomes &quot;my neighbor&quot; and the epicenter becomes &quot;my hometown&quot;. That's an OOC reason, but nonetheless a reason. I wouldn't be scared of these if they were somewhere else entirely.</span></p>
<p>It seems that these have become unredacted since I started typing this. I liked it better before. Not changing my upvote, but still.</p>

